The paper deals with coinductive reasoning in Horn clause logic, which is a topic that falls under the area of logic and automated reasoning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). Additionally, the paper discusses the extension of Miller et al's framework of uniform proofs, which is a topic related to programming languages and compilers (cs.PL) and computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also mentions the construction of infinite data, which is a topic related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and formal languages and automata theory (cs.LF).
